Normalized Citation Rate (NCR
y )—the ratio between the Number of Citations on a specific infectious disease d and the total number of citations about medicine or biology in year y (to determine which papers, we used the MAG fields of study).
(1) \documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{upgreek} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document} }{}\begin{equation*} \mathrm{NCR}_{y}(d) = \frac{\sum _{\lbrace i \in P | p_{\mathrm{Year}}=y \mbox{ and } i_{\mathrm{Disease}}=d\rbrace }\sum _{\lbrace j \in P \rbrace } j \in i_{\mathrm{citations}}}{|\lbrace j \in P | j_{\mathrm{Year}}=y\rbrace j_{\mathrm{citations}}|} \end{equation*}\end{document}
